# Extraction doc bug fixes (NVBug / QA)

**26.05 release:** also follow `.cursor/rules/nrl-26.05-release-docs.mdc` (critical errors + pre-merge greps from Randy's PR #2074 review).

When fixing documentation drift from a bug ticket, **place each fact once** — do not repeat deployment detail on every file the bug mentions.

## Page roles (26.05 extraction docs)

| Page | Put here | Do NOT put here |
|------|----------|-----------------|
| `prerequisites-support-matrix.md` | Helm `nimOperator.*`, default NIMs, GPU/disk table, Omni caption guidance, `nvcr.io` image pins |
| `multimodal-extraction.md` | Pipeline behavior, API flags (`extract_charts` defaults on, etc.) — concepts only | Model deploy IDs, Helm flags, `nimOperator`, NIM names as deploy guidance |
| `nemo_retriever/helm/README.md` | Chart NIM enablement, removed NIMs, caption/chart deploy for 26.05 | Conceptual extraction tutorials |
| `nemo_retriever/docs/cli/README.md` | CLI examples, flag names, one-line caveats | Full Helm deploy guides; duplicate support-matrix tables |
| `nemo_retriever/README.md` | Package quickstart examples only | Same as CLI — link to published docs for deploy |

**Rule:** If a paragraph mentions `nimOperator`, chart defaults, or "not in the Helm chart", it almost certainly belongs only in `prerequisites-support-matrix.md` (or `nemo_retriever/helm/README.md` for chart-only bugs).

## Workflow

1. Read the bug **Expected result** as a checklist of facts, not text to paste into every file.
2. Edit **only** files listed in the bug (or the user prompt). No drive-by edits.
3. Other pages: one sentence + markdown link to the owning section (e.g. `[Image captioning (26.05)](prerequisites-support-matrix.md#image-captioning-2605)`).
4. **Minimal diff** — no new sections unless the bug requires them; no "26.05 release" boilerplate on unrelated headings.
5. Before finishing: grep your diff for `nimOperator`, `Helm chart`, `nvcr.io` outside `prerequisites-support-matrix.md` and `nemo_retriever/helm/` — remove or move.

## Common 26.05 facts (verify in code/chart, do not invent)

- Chart/infographic path: `nemotron-page-elements-v3` + OCR; **not** graphic-elements / yolox in Helm `values.yaml`.
- Captioning: supported = `nemotron-3-nano-omni-30b-a3b-reasoning` only. **Do not mention** `nemotron-nano-12b-v2-vl` (removed; never 26.05 Helm). Removal narrative → release notes only if needed.
- Hosted OCR in CLI/README examples: `nemotron-ocr-v1` until v2 NIM is published on build.nvidia.com.
- `extract_charts` and `extract_infographics` default **on** in `ExtractParams` — do not document as off by default.

